Tanzania's public debt reached 60.9trn/- in April this year having jumped from 55.5trn/- last year, Finance and Planning MInister Dr. Mwigulu Nchemba announced on Thurday when presenting the 2020 National State of Economy and the National Development Plan. According to the Minister, the external debt reached 43.7trn/- and 17.3trn/- domestic debt. He said the national debt is still sustainable for both short, medium, and long term, basing on all internationally accepted debt sustainability indicators.